<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Direct distribution (Developer ID + notarization), NOT the App Sandbox.
      The sandbox is intentionally dropped: a multi-service browser needs broad
      file/network access that the sandbox makes awkward. Hardened Runtime stays
      ON (ENABLE_HARDENED_RUNTIME = YES) because notarization requires it.

      Only Hardened Runtime resource-access entitlements belong here now. The
      former sandbox keys (app-sandbox, network.client/server,
      files.user-selected, print, personal-information.photos-library) are
      no-ops outside the sandbox and have been removed.

      Camera + microphone are declared so embedded services (huddles, calls)
      can request capture once a WKUIDelegate media-capture handler is wired up.
      They pair with NSCameraUsageDescription / NSMicrophoneUsageDescription
      in Info.plist. See DISTRIBUTION.md.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.device.camera</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
